item.title: [HBASE-12123] Failed assertion in BucketCache after HBASE-11331
item.description:
As reported by Enis Soztutar

We are still running with assertions on in tests, and this block is failing the assertion. Seems important: 


        if (data instanceof HFileBlock) {

          ByteBuffer sliceBuf = ((HFileBlock) data).getBufferReadOnlyWithHeader();

          sliceBuf.rewind();

          assert len == sliceBuf.limit() + HFileBlock.EXTRA_SERIALIZATION_SPACE;
item.summary: Failed assertion in BucketCache after HBASE-11331

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: This assertion needs to be updated or removed. It does not account for the possible presence of the next block's header. Seems to me that BucketCache need not be this familiar with the intimate details of HFileBlock.
This patch works as intended. Conveniently, it applies across 0.98+.

SmallTests and io.hfile.* pass locally for me. Pushed to 0.98+
